The employees say it comes at a time when unemployment in the country is escalating. National party spokesperson, Pule Mabe, is reported to have made the call for the ANC to start the implementation of a section 189 process to restore its financial health. The ANC, which is essentially broke and has been struggling to pay its workers on time, has a huge tax and provident fund debt. ANC staff are engaged in a protracted stayaway due to outstanding salaries. --ChannelAfrica--